            <h2 class="section-title">üí° Current Market Assessment & Action Items</h2>
            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.1); border-color: #10b981;">
                <h3 style="color: #10b981;">üá∫üá∏ United States: Strong Buy Signal for Swing Traders</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> $398B Sep inflow (highest 2024), $204B Oct, $160B Nov. Long-term securities purchases at $263B.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Long SPY/QQQ on 2-5% pullbacks. Target 2-4 week swings. Stop below recent swing low.<br>
                    <strong>Best Sectors:</strong> Tech (QQQ), Financials (XLF), Large-cap Growth.<br>
                    <strong>Risk:</strong> Low. NFCI at -0.48 = loose conditions supporting rally.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1); border-color: #ef4444;">
                <h3 style="color: #ef4444;">üá®üá≥ China: Avoid Long Exposure / Consider Shorts</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> Record portfolio outflows since 2022, FDI weakening, H1 2024 outflows resumed.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Avoid BABA, JD, PDD, BIDU. Consider KWEB put spreads or short via inverse ETFs.<br>
                    <strong>Alternative:</strong> If bullish on Asia, play India (INDA) or ex-China EM (EMXC) instead.<br>
                    <strong>Wait for:</strong> 2-3 months of sustained inflows before considering longs.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1); border-color: #667eea;">
                <h3 style="color: #667eea;">üåè Emerging Markets (ex-China): Selective Swing Opportunities</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>Evidence:</strong> $903B projected 2024 inflows (+32% YoY), portfolio flows at 3-year highs.<br>
                    <strong>Trade:</strong> Long EEM (but watch China weight), INDA (India pure play), EWZ (Brazil).<br>
                    <strong>Duration:</strong> 4-8 week swings. These are longer timeframe trades than US.<br>
                    <strong>Best Plays:</strong> India (demographics + tech growth) and Brazil (commodity cycle).
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box" style="background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1); border-color: #f59e0b;">
                <h3 style="color: #f59e0b;">‚ö†Ô∏è Risks to Monitor</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>1. Flow Reversal:</strong> If US TIC data turns negative for 2+ consecutive months = major red flag.<br>
                    <strong>2. Core PCE Acceleration:</strong> Above 3% could force Fed to pause cuts or even hike.<br>
                    <strong>3. NFCI Turns Positive:</strong> Would signal tightening financial conditions = bearish.<br>
                    <strong>4. Geopolitical Shocks:</strong> Can override fundamentals temporarily. Use stops.
                </p>
            </div>
